				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Unless the HO is well coordinated, I am not sure they are entirely worth it.
<br />

<br />
I don't know how everyone else plays, but I am constantly clicking spells/abilities.  (I played a Bard in EQ1, and I'll bet I'm "twisting" just as much in this game).  So, if you suspend the entire group for say 5 seconds, how much damage did the group lose as a result?  I'm not sure of the damage of all the classes yet, but to have a full group lose one spell/ability worth of damage each to wait for one HO to have a possibility to hit may be a net loss.
<br />

<br />
The above post appears to be the most efficient group I've seen.  For the most part, any 'pick-up' group I've been in, completion of an HO is a matter of Luck and is Random at best.
<br />

<br />
I'm not saying they aren't worth doing, but there needs to be an efficient and easy way to make these work when playing with different folks.  Unless I'm missing something in my calculations?
<br />

<br />
Happy Gaming,
<br />
Singza
<br />

<br />

<br />
PS - Since I'm not good a programing hot buttons, could someone please show a sample for a Macro, including the command for a timed pause?</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
